   "source": [
    "### Understanding Embedding Shape\n",
    "\n",
    "The shape **(5, 384)** means that **five** input texts were processed, and each text was converted into a **384-dimensional** dense vector. \n",
    "\n",
    "These vectors capture the **semantic meaning** of the text. Because they are numerical representations, they can be used for various downstream tasks such as:\n",
    "- **Semantic Search:** Finding documents related to a query by comparing vector distances.\n",
    "- **Similarity Analysis:** Identifying how similar two pieces of text are.\n",
    "- **Recommendation Systems:** Suggesting books based on the proximity of their embedding vectors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
