    "### Semantic Search vs. Keyword Matching\n",
    "\n",
    "The results above demonstrate **semantic search**. Unlike traditional keyword-based search (which looks for exact word matches like \"gripping\" or \"civilisations\"), semantic search uses the vector embeddings to find texts that are **conceptually similar** to the query.\n",
    "\n",
    "Even if the query uses different words than the corpus, the model understands the underlying themes (e.g., \"space\", \"aliens\", \"interstellar\") and retrieves the most relevant matches based on their position in the 384-dimensional vector space."
